<br>
The spawn exists to provide adventure. Part of that adventure is the hopes of obtaining the container needed to make ragefire's heart.<br>
<br>
Ragefire does not equal ragefire's heart. He does equal the aspiration of obtaining that heart.<br>
<br>
I personally think that such a pivotal mob despawning because it got aggroed and lost aggro is a flaw in Verant's planning, not something to blame on a valiant effort to kill the dragon.<br>
<br>
My experience with despawning mobs is that most mobs that despawn after losing aggro are quest triggered mobs. Ragefire is not triggered.<br>
