<br>
But, I have some comments regarding some thoughts in this thread:<br>
<br>
RF despawned with his bag, so that's one less cleric epic, one more cleric in the bottleneck. From shooting the shit with other people in game, conventional wisdom is now that the cleric epic quest is: get RF bag, and run around with a few friends and grab some misc. pieces. So that's why there's so much interest in this thread I think. The cleric epic is extremely valuable and desired, but here's one that didn't happen and was &quot;wasted&quot;. This is seperate from how fun and rewarding the experience was for everybody involved. I wasn't involved, not really any of my damn business, but that's how I see it.<br>
<br>
There is no &quot;ten minute rule&quot; to the best of my knowledge. Most mobs never despawn. Some mobs despawn if not engaged for some amount of time, maybe 10 minutes. Some mobs will despawn a set amount of time after they spawn. Some mobs will despawn for no apparant reason whatsoever, other than maybe to piss you off.<br>
<br>
Don't believe me? Try doing the quest for the 9th Coldain Ring. Don't worry, you don't need the 8th ring to do the quest, only to collect your reward at the time. As far as I know, any of the 5 mobs (dorf traitors) that you need to kill will despawn if you don't kill them quicly enough, even if they are locked in combat at the moment. The most notorious is the ArchBich Peffin Ambersnow in EW. Have fun making another TAA when the bitch hoses you.<br>
<br>
Is RF despawning a bug? I doubt it. But even if it is a bug, so what? RF despawns, for real, as was proven here. And if this really is a bug and VI gets around to fixing it, I assume they will announce it in a patch message, as they always do when they try to fix something.<br>
<br>
Since RF despawns, players are simply not allowed to extend huge courtesy here. Some nice cleric camps it for 5 days, but needs 3 hours to gather and organize troops before attacking, then needs to rez up and try again. Even if everybody else on the server graciously bows out - too bad, you lose, RF despawns. I see now that the reality will be that if you don't kill RF in reasonable time, somebody else will move in, or it'll just despawn and nobody gets the bag.<br>
<br>
The camp is much different, no more FGs to clear to maintain the camp and get RF to spawn. But sure, even though it's a new camp, clerics can still respect the camper. Personally I think it's silly to man a spawn point that won't activate for 4-5 days, but if clerics feel that's how they want to run this silly thing, good luck to them all. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uxorgogorgonzolo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xorgo Gorgonzolo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/1/02 10:34:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3098.topic&index=80>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oops</span><hr size=1> From what I've read on eqcleric and witnessed the dragon form of Ragefire can despawn (hes like Ixiblat Fer) but Im almost positive the human form wont. (I had accidentally aggrod the human form coming down to help affliction last time they took him down about 45 min before their attempt)<br>
<br>
Once he heals to full you probably have about 10 min to reaggro him and kite him around.  I was going to offer to do this with my druid for Vivix but he was still hurt and summoning from far off when I approached the NE fireglobe.<br>
<br>
This ragefire is on a 5-6 day timer instead of 2-3 so I got to think there is a more humane alternative to the camp system we have.  There is nothing worse than a 5-6 day camp than one that got ganked though -- hopefully everyone will respect camp per solb if that trend continues in skyfire.  <br>
